    <section id="id1167176194724">
      <title>A GRID NETWORK</title>
      <list id="id1167178309903" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>To indicate the location of a specific place or characteristic is much easier if there is a grid network. These are lines drawn on the map, which divide the map into small squares. At the top of the map, each square is then numbered 1, 2, 3, and so on. In the left and/or right margins, you find the letters A, B, C, etc.</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id1167178274505">We then use these letters and numbers to give each square a name.</para>
      <para id="id1167178142776">Example:</para>
